Yes. The charting part is only the beachhead.

The real prize is a clinical cognition co-pilot built around nursing reality instead of forcing nurses to serve the EHR.

The core premise

A perfect nursing AI should do three things at once:

It should watch the stream, compress the truth, and defend the nurse’s time.

In practical terms:

care happens
→ AI observes and structures it
→ nurse verifies, edits, approves
→ chart updates everywhere it should

The nurse should not become a clerk for the machine.
The machine should become a scribe, organizer, lookout, translator, and shield.

