Trust and safety model

This is where most systems fail.

Allowed
	•	draft notes
	•	pre-fill flowsheets
	•	extract observations
	•	summarize shifts
	•	surface gaps
	•	recommend likely documentation destinations
	•	detect patterns worth review

Never allowed
	•	fabricate assessments
	•	sign entries
	•	backfill care not evidenced
	•	silently alter timestamps
	•	hide uncertainty
	•	give autonomous medical orders
	•	override nurse edits

Confidence labeling

Every suggestion should show:
	•	source
	•	confidence
	•	whether direct or inferred

Example:
	•	BP 128/78 — direct from connected vitals machine
	•	Patient anxious — inferred from nurse note + repeated call requests
	•	Ambulated 100 ft — estimated from hallway sensor + nurse voice note, confirm

